        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 21 at 10:44PM MDT until July 21 at 11:00PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 1044 PM MDT, A severe thunderstorm was located 19 miles northeast
of Ballantine, or 34 miles southeast of Roundup, moving east at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Two inch hail and 60 mph wind gusts, along with very
heavy rain and frequent lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect
wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Mainly rural areas of Northeastern Yellowstone County, north of
Interstate 94.

This warning does NOT include the city of Billings.
</description>
        <instruction>Anyone outdoors should move to shelter inside a well-built structure
and stay away from windows. This storm is capable of producing
dangerous hail and damaging winds.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead
to flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
